translated:
Kaiser, Erik, M.D., Gothenburg, born on August 20, 1892 in Stockholm, son of merchant Eduard K. and Thérèse Bensow^. Married to Karin Charlotta Eisner. Children: Ragnar, born in 1921, law graduate, Marianne, born in 1925, textile consultant. Completed high school in Stockholm in 1910, earned a Bachelor of Medicine degree from the Caroline Institute in 1915, and a medical license in 1919. Assistant in Anatomy at the Caroline Institute in 1915, temporary assistant physician at Eskilstuna Hospital in 1917, assistant physician at Seraf Central Hospital Surgical Clinic in 1918, temporary assistant physician at Stockholm Epidemic Hospital in 1919, at Skellefteå Hospital in 1919, at Ängelholm Hospital from 1919 to 1920, assistant physician at Holtermanska Hospital from 1920 to 1923, temporary chief physician there for three months, assisting physician at Gothenburg City Polyclinic for Dermatology and Venereology from 1933 to 1934, physician there in 1934, physician on Swedish America Line ships for short periods in 1921, 1924, and 1926, practicing physician in Gothenburg since 1923.

Kalén, Helge Olov Efraim, dentist, Norrköping, born on May 13, 1907 in Tingstad, Östergötland County, son of primary school teacher Albert K. and Emma Andersson. Married to Dagmar Walman. Children: Ulla Britt, born in 1929, Ragnar, born in 1936, Lena-Kari, born in 1938. Completed high school in Norrköping in 1925, earned a dental degree in 1926, and became a dentist in 1929. Practiced in Hallstavik from 1929 to 1930, in Hudiksvall from 1930 to 1932, and in Norrköping since 1933.

Kalén, Herbert Johannes, rector, Gothenburg, born on June 21, 1893 in Gothenburg, son of rector Frithiof K. and Lizzie Frost. Married in 1923 to Vera Pattison. Son: Roger, born in 1927. Completed high school at Gothenburg Latin School in 1911, earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in Gothenburg in 1914, a Master of Arts in 1917, a Licentiate of Philosophy in 1921, and a Doctorate of Philosophy in 1923. Studied at the University of Jena in 1913, Oxford University in 1919, and in Dijon and Paris from 1928 to 1929. Foundation year at Gothenburg Real School in 1922-1923. Traveled to Germany, England, France, Norway, Denmark, the Netherlands, Belgium, Austria, and Italy multiple times between 1912 and 1939, and again in 1945 and 1946. Taught at Rodhe's School in Gothenburg from 1911 to 1922, substitute teacher at Gothenburg School of Commerce from 1917 to 1920 and from 1921 to 1922, extra lecturer at Uddevalla Municipality Gymnasium from 1923 to 1927, adjunct at Linköping Higher Primary School from 1927 to 1929, at Gothenburg Real School from 1929 to 1931, lecturer in English and French at Gothenburg School of Commerce since 1931, rector there since 1941. Hourly teacher at Gothenburg Girls' Gymnasium from 1930 to 1932, organizer and instructor of summer courses for Swedish school youths in Oxford and Bournemouth from 1923 to 1929, and instructor of summer courses in English for primary school teachers in 1945. Revised Gothenburg University, member of the Gothenburg School of Commerce board, Gothenburg Practical Mid-level College, and the Anglo-Swedish Society in Gothenburg. Writings: A Middle-English Metrical Paraphrase of the Old Testament (doctoral dissertation, 1923), Grammar exercises book in English for business language (1937), An English commercial reader (with glossary and commentary, 1935), Graduation exam in English for commercial school (1945), articles and reviews in journals and magazines. Hobbies: literature, philately, travel, skiing. Received the Order of the Polar Star.

Kalén, Eva Agda Ingeborg, dentist, Motala, born on August 20, 1902 in Tingstad, Östergötland County, daughter of primary school teacher Albert K. and Emma Andersson. Completed high school in Eslöv in 1922, earned a dental degree in 1925, and became a dentist in 1927. Worked temporarily in Sollefteå from 1927 to 1928, and has been practicing in Motala since 1928.

Kalén, Ingemar Eskil Johan, Bachelor of Arts, city librarian, Tranås, born on October 28, 1917 in Varberg, son of primary school teacher Johan K. and Theres Boman. Married in 1944 to Inger Cars. Children: Kerstin, born in 1945, Johan, born in 1946. Completed high school in 1937, earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in 1943, passed the examination in library studies in 1945. City librarian in Tranås since 1945. Board member of the Swedish Folk Librarians Association since 1945.
